{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel B serve-side echo for the round-trip proof. Blocks on the request eventfd (fd3); when a requester rings it, writes a fixed marker reply (ok) into the portal region (reply length at region[0], bytes at region+8) using duplicate-octet-range-inside-buffer, then rings the response eventfd (fd4). Demonstrates cross-process region writes plus the doorbell round-trip; the real tool-run replaces the fixed marker with execute-pinned-helper-matching-operation-identifier output. Additive Channel B; does not touch Channel A.","module_name":"serve-portal-region-request-writing-marker-reply","package_name":"serve-portal-region-request-writing-marker-reply","function_definitions":{"serve-portal-region-request-writing-marker-reply":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"unused0","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"unused1","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"marker","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"ok"},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"base","name":"g_portal_r